The average value of \(BC\) over all permutations is \(\frac{2 \times 3}{6 \times 5} = \frac{6}{30} = \frac{1}{5}\). 3. **Average value of \(DEF\)**: - The sum of the products of the roots taken three at a time is \(-5\). Each unordered triplet \(\{D, E, F\}\) is counted 6 times in permutations, so the total sum over all ordered triplets is \(6 \times (-5) = -30\). The average value of \(DEF\) is \(\frac{-30}{720} = -\frac{1}{24}\). Combining these results: \[ -\frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{5} - \frac{1}{24} \] Converting to a common denominator (120): \[ -\frac{40}{120} + \frac{24}{120} - \frac{5}{120} = \frac{-40 + 24 - 5}{120} = \frac{-21}{120} = -\frac{7}{40} \] Thus, the average value of \(A + BC + DEF\) over all permutations is \(\boxed{-\dfrac{7}{40}}\).
